Registrations have opened for the 2019 MyBroadband Fibre Conference, which will take place on 17 July at The Venue in Houghton Estate. This exclusive technical conference will focus on South African fibre networks and networking technologies. The event is aimed at IT executives and professionals who want to learn more about the latest developments in the South African fibre market. Delegates will learn more about fibre network rollouts, long distance fibre networks, fibre backbones for mobile networks, and the latest technology trends. The MC for the event is Radio 702â€™s Aki Anastasiou who will be joined by excellent speakers, including SEACOM CDO Suveer Ramdhani and Octotel CEO Rob Gilmour. For more information about the conference, visit the 2019 Fibre Conference website.